Freeport-McMoRan Inc (FCX) Analysts See $0.19 EPS


					

						July 24, 2017 - By Louis Casey


Investors sentiment decreased to 0.96 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.02, from 0.98 in 2016Q3. It is negative, as 61 investors sold Freeport-McMoRan Inc shares while 223 reduced holdings. 99 funds opened positions while 175 raised stakes. 995.10 million shares or 5.90% more from 939.67 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported.
 33,124 are held by Paradigm Advsr Lc. Blackrock Fund Advisors accumulated 0.06% or 24.55M shares. Neuberger Berman Limited Liability invested in 87,985 shares or 0% of the stock. Blb&B Advisors Ltd Liability Com holds 68,578 shares. Nikko Asset Americas invested in 1.76 million shares. Tctc Holding Lc has invested 0.32% in Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX). Highbridge Cap Management Lc has 163,851 shares. Marshwinds Advisory Com invested in 12,701 shares. 733,733 were accumulated by Teacher Retirement Systems Of Texas. Point72 Asset Mngmt Ltd Partnership holds 702,200 shares or 0.06% of its portfolio. Violich Capital Management Inc reported 27,000 shares. United Fire Grp Inc Inc holds 0.05% or 10,000 shares in its portfolio. Company Of Vermont holds 0% of its portfolio in Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) for 757 shares. Commonwealth Bancorporation Of Aus holds 0.05% in Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) or 325,627 shares. Hourglass Capital Ltd Llc reported 219,500 shares.

Since February 1, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 4 sales for $2.34 million activity. WHITMIRE C DONALD JR sold $38,425 worth of stock or 2,525 shares. Another trade for 14,000 shares valued at $232,498 was made by MADONNA JON C/ on Wednesday, February 1. $1.18 million worth of Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) was sold by Conger Harry M. IV on Wednesday, February 15.






 Analysts expect Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) to report $0.19 EPS on July, 25 before the open.They anticipate $0.21 EPS change or 1,050.00 % from last quarter’s $-0.02 EPS. FCX’s profit would be $274.27M giving it 17.12 P/E if the $0.19 EPS is correct. After having $0.15 EPS previously, Freeport-McMoRan Inc’s analysts see 26.67 % EPS growth. The stock decreased 0.23% or $0.03 on July 21, reaching $13.01. About shares traded. Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) has risen 6.83% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 9.87% the S&P500.
Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) Ratings Coverage
Among 21 analysts covering Freeport-McMoran Copper & Gold (NYSE:FCX), 5 have Buy rating, 5 Sell and 11 Hold. Therefore 24% are positive. Freeport-McMoran Copper & Gold had 68 analyst reports since July 28, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Cowen & Co maintained Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) on Monday, May 16 with “Outperform” rating. Jefferies maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Thursday, June 8 report. Deutsche Bank downgraded Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) rating on Tuesday, February 21. Deutsche Bank has “Sell” rating and $12.50 target. The stock has “Hold” rating by Jefferies on Tuesday, January 12. The company was initiated on Friday, September 18 by FBR Capital. On Tuesday, May 17 the stock rating was upgraded by Jefferies to “Buy”. The stock of Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) earned “Hold” rating by Argus Research on Wednesday, February 3. The firm has “Buy” rating by Cowen & Co given on Monday, July 17. The stock of Freeport-McMoRan Inc (NYSE:FCX) earned “Mkt Perform” rating by FBR Capital on Friday, February 3. The rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets with “Sector Perform” on Tuesday, October 27.
Freeport-McMoRan Inc. is a mining company. The company has market cap of $18.78 billion. The Firm operates through geographical assets with proven and probable reserves of copper, gold and molybdenum, and traded copper producer. It has a 41.77 P/E ratio. The Company’s divisions include refined copper products, copper in concentrate, gold, molybdenum, oil and other.
