Who We Are





Who we Are 
Our Industry Standing 
Our Leadership
Our History
Doing Business with Us
Contact Us













Freeport-McMoRan Inc. (FCX) is a natural resources company with headquarters in Phoenix, Arizona. FCX operates large, long-lived, geographically diverse assets with significant proven and probable reserves of copper, gold, and molybdenum. FCX is the world’s largest publicly traded copper producer, the world’s largest producer of molybdenum, and a significant gold producer. 
FCX's portfolio of metal assets includes the Grasberg minerals district in Indonesia, one of the world's largest copper and gold deposits; significant mining operations in the Americas, including the large-scale Morenci minerals district in North America and the Cerro Verde operation in South America.    
Our global workforce includes over 50,000 employees and contractors worldwide. FCX has a strong commitment to safety performance, environmental management and to the local communities where it operates. FCX is a founding member of the International Council on Mining and Metals (ICMM) and committed to implementation of the ICMM Sustainable Development Framework.    
Our stock trades on the New York Stock Exchange under the  ticker symbol “FCX". 
 
